body:
@nakul02, @deroneriksson 

I believe this fixes the issue with PR #61 with regards to both keeping the history of the `CustomErrorListener` and allowing all 3 commits to compile.  All of the main work has been squashed into the first commit, and the next two commits only involve the refactoring from `CustomErrorListener` as an inner class of `SyntacticErrorListener` to a full outer class.  Note, that we will still need to commit all 3 commits to the repo to maintain the history.

Please have a look and see if everything checks out.

Deleted Token and ParseException classes. Changed all ParseException references to DMLParseException.

@mboehm7 The only real change in code functionality is in DMLParseException, where newMsg code was replaced my msg code. Please let me know if this looks OK or needs to be changed and if other code updates are needed.

Tests completed successfully [here](https://sparktc.ibmcloud.com/jenkins/job/SystemML-OnDemand/40/).
